    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@U01R76LELBT> You can program quantum stuff in simulators. In real quantum computers, the standard gates are realized in hardware and they are linked by modifiable connections, which are more like wires than like software. Today's quantum computers are so small that classical computers plus attached hardware can easily create the illusion of programmability, but this is much like having robots change wires in a circuit board.",
